{
  "texts": [
    "End-users, such as clients and customers, require local explanations since they are concerned with decisions directly affecting them; this local need is also reinforced by the \"right to explanation\" (Goodman and Flaxman, 2017).",
    "Similarly, physicians using NLP systems must rely on local explanations.",
    "On the other hand, business decision-makers and scientists generally favor global explanations, which help identify broader trends and underlying patterns.",
    "From a social perspective, global explanations hold more significance.",
    "However, accumulating local evidence can progressively provide insights into global tendencies."
  ]
}